study_description: A collection of de novo variants identified in collections of families with autism. This dataset includes: - **SD_autism_ssc** A collection of de novo variants identified in the Simons Simplex Collection. - **SD_EichlerTG2012_liftover** Targeted resequencing of 44 genes in 2446 ASD probands reported in O'Roak et al., *Science*, 2012. - **SD_EichlerWE2012_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 667 individual exomes from 209 simplex families reported in O’Roak, B. et al., *Nature* 2012. - **SD_IossifovWE2014_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of more than 2,500 simplex families, each having a child with an autistic spectrum disorder reported in Iossifov, I. et al., *Nature*, 2014.. - **SD_Krumm2015_SNVindel_liftover** A set of exonic single-nucleotide variants (SNVs) from 2,377 families with autism reported in Krumm, N. et al., *Nat Genet*, 2015. - **SD_ORoakTG2014_SSC_liftover** Resequencing of 64 candidate neurodevelopmental disorder risk genes in 5,979 individuals - 3,486 probands and 2,493 unaffected siblings reported in O'Roak, B. et al., *Nat Commun*, 2014. - **SD_SFARI_SSC_WGS_CSHL_DENOVO** Whole genome sequence (WGS) of simplex families from the Simons Simplex Collection (SSC) reported in Yoon, S. et al., *Commun Biol*, 2021. - **SD_Turner2017_liftover** Genome sequence data from 516 idiopathic autism families (2,064 individuals) reported in Turner T. et al., *Cell*, 2017. - **SD_Werling2018_liftover** Whole genome sequencing data from 519 autism spectrum disorder families reported in Werling, D.M. et al., *Nat Genet*, 2018. - **SD_autism_spark** A collection of de novo variants identified in the SPARK Collection. - **SD_iWES_v1_1_genotypes_DENOVO** Whole-exome sequencing of saliva DNA from more than 30,000 SPARK families. - **SD_autism_other** A collection of de novo variants identified in various collections of families with ASD. - **SD_ACS2014_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 3,871 autism cases and 9,937 ancestry-matched or parental controls reported in De Rubeis S. et al., *Nature*, 2014. - **SD_AGRE_WG38_859_DENOVO** Whole genome sequence (WGS) of multiplex families from the Autism Genetic Resource Exchange (AGRE) reported in Yoon, S. et al., *Commun Biol*, 2021. - **SD_ORoakTG2014_TASC_liftover** Resequencing of 64 candidate neurodevelopmental disorder risk genes in 5,979 individuals - 3,486 probands and 2,493 unaffected siblings reported in O'Roak, B. et al., *Nat Commun*, 2014.. - **SD_Yuen2017_liftover** Whole genome sequencing of 5,205 samples from families with ASD reported in C Yuen R., et al., *Nat Neurosci*, 2017. - **SD_Takata2018_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 262 ASD probands of Japanese origin reported in Takata A. et al., *Cell Reports*, 2018.
